reviewText: I like Diedrich Bader (loved him as Oswald on the Drew Carey Show) so I selected this mindless piece of fluff to relax late night with. The acting is campy, and the script written for a juvenile mind. The two bumbling alien conquerors are so pathetic that you feel sorry they can't cut off your head. Think of it this way, if you watched a good sci-fi movie and wanted to reenact it in your living room for friends, you would end up with something like this.
Title: N/A

reviewText: EVIL ALIEN CONQUERERS is the story of two superior beings from another world who come to Earth in order to kill everyone. Unfortunately for them, they are A) Idiots. And B) Unarmed. No problem! With the aid of a slacker named Kenny, My-ik (Diedrich Bader) and Du-ug (Chris Parnell) will come up w/ a master plan to destroy the puny, inferior humans! EAC is hilariously, ridiculously funny from start to finish! I find myself quoting it in my sleep! Many will find the humor to be "stupid", "inane", or even "retarded". I myself found it a simple joy to watch, especially once the mighty Croker "I am 100 feet tall!" shows up in miniaturized form! So, if you are one of those lucky enough to enjoy silly for silly's sake, then you'll probably love this movie...
Title: N/A

reviewText: A truly mediocre comedy finds "The Drew Carry Show"'s Diedrich Bader and "Saturday Night Live"'s Chris Parnell as a pair of inept aliens from the planet Kabijj sent to behead all 6 billion humans in 2-1/2 days. Befriended by burger-jockey Michael Weston, they are soon seduced by Earth's pleasures, represented by scads of unsubtle product-placements. Basically, an unfunny, 90-minute comercial for Smirnoff Ice, with some half-hearted pratfalls tossed in to keep us from dozing off.
summary: Hopelessly inept aliens try to conquer Palmdale!

reviewText: You'll either love or you'll hate, but THIS MOVIE IS HILARIOUS!!!!  This movie takes stupid comedy to the next level.  The story follows 2 idiot alien invaders sent to Earth from the planet Cabbige.  Mi'ike, & Do'ug need to destroy the human race in like 48 hours or another big alien named Kroger will eat them.  Now had the makers of this film taken this plot seriously this movie woulda sucked, they didn't though and what ensues is pure comic genious.  Seriously, "Stupid Funny" has never been done so good.  I've tried to show off this movie to alot of different people, and the reactions afterwards are always mixed, people either get it, or they don't.  I hope you'll get it, this movie is bound to be a classic.
summary: YOU WILL DIE IN AGONY RON!!!

reviewText: Best low budget comedy in years.  Cleverly immature and riddled with great one-liners and sight gags.  Pay no heed to the naysayers...this probably isn't their style of movie anyway.  As a testament to the lowbrow quality of this movie, Tori Spelling (Jan the Unibrow) refused to appear in the credits.  That makes it a keeper in my book.  At the very least, rent this movie and behold the Kabijjian magnificence for yourself.Enthuse for Rabirr!
